@eht16 It is hard to say what is commonly used.

The [Python Logging Cookbook](https://docs.python.org/3/howto/logging-cookbook.html#multiple-handlers-and-formatters) does set fomatters for each handler using the `setFormatter` method. Personally, I think that using a logging configuration passed to `dictConfig` is the best way, and the current implementation of `AsynchronousLogstashHandler` works fine with that.

